.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH daft 1  "daft " 
.SH NAME
daft \- A Git extensions toolkit for worktree\-based development
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdaft\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fIsubcommands\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
daft is a comprehensive Git extensions toolkit that enhances developer workflows with powerful worktree management. It provides both git\-style subcommands (git worktree\-clone, git worktree\-checkout, ...) and short verb aliases (daft clone, daft go, daft start, ...).
.PP
Run \*(Aqdaft\*(Aq with no arguments to see a categorized command overview.
.PP
GETTING STARTED
.PP
Clone a repository into a worktree layout:
.PP
	daft clone <url>
.PP
Or adopt an existing repository:
.PP
	daft adopt
.PP
Switch to a branch (each branch gets its own directory):
.PP
	daft go <branch>
.PP
Create a new branch:
.PP
	daft start <branch>
.PP
SHELL INTEGRATION
.PP
Enable automatic cd into new worktrees:
.PP
	eval "$(daft shell\-init zsh)"
.PP
See daft\-shell\-init(1) for details.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
daft\-clone(1)
Clone a repository into a worktree\-based directory structure
.TP
daft\-init(1)
Initialize a new repository in the worktree\-based directory structure
.TP
daft\-adopt(1)
Convert a traditional repository to worktree\-based layout
.TP
daft\-go(1)
Open a worktree for an existing branch, or create one with \-b
.TP
daft\-start(1)
Create a new branch and worktree
.TP
daft\-carry(1)
Transfer uncommitted changes to other worktrees
.TP
daft\-list(1)
List all worktrees with status information
.TP
daft\-remove(1)
Delete branches and their worktrees
.TP
daft\-rename(1)
Rename a branch and move its worktree
.TP
daft\-prune(1)
Remove worktrees and branches for deleted remote branches
.TP
daft\-update(1)
Update worktree branches from their remote tracking branches
.TP
daft\-sync(1)
Synchronize worktrees with remote (prune + update all)
.TP
daft\-eject(1)
Convert a worktree\-based repository back to traditional layout
.TP
daft\-shared(1)
Manage shared files across worktrees
.TP
daft\-hooks(1)
Manage repository trust for hook execution
.TP
daft\-layout(1)
Manage worktree layouts
.TP
daft\-multi\-remote(1)
Manage multi\-remote worktree organization
.TP
daft\-config(1)
Configure remote sync behavior
.TP
daft\-doctor(1)
Diagnose daft installation and configuration issues
.TP
daft\-shell\-init(1)
Generate shell wrapper functions for daft commands
.TP
daft\-setup(1)
Add daft shell integration to your shell config
.TP
daft\-shortcuts(1)
Manage command shortcut symlinks
.TP
daft\-release\-notes(1)
Display release notes from the changelog
.TP
daft\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
